1
00:00:01,190 --> 00:00:12,080
♪

2
00:00:12,080 --> 00:00:15,160
(singing foreign language)

3
00:00:15,160 --> 00:01:33,020
♪

4
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,290
(indistinct conversations)

5
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:46,140
♪

6
00:01:46,140 --> 00:01:49,110
Hey, let's go in there and
see the two-headed snake!

7
00:01:49,110 --> 00:01:51,130
Let's pick a show that
we all agree on, okay?

8
00:01:51,130 --> 00:01:52,210
-Okay, that one!
-This one!

9
00:01:52,210 --> 00:01:54,040
(chuckles)

10
00:01:54,040 --> 00:01:56,250
You guys are impossible
when it comes to decisions.

11
00:01:56,250 --> 00:01:57,260
Whoa, what a crowd.

12
00:01:57,260 --> 00:01:59,180
Why do we always have
to do what you want?

13
00:01:59,180 --> 00:02:01,150
We better hurry up or
we won't see anything.

14
00:02:01,150 --> 00:02:02,190
You're stupid.

15
00:02:02,190 --> 00:02:05,070
And you're a punk whose got
a little pea for a brain.

16
00:02:05,070 --> 00:02:09,140
Hey, would you two
please stop arguing?

17
00:02:09,140 --> 00:02:10,210
Oh, hey, let's go there.

18
00:02:10,210 --> 00:02:12,050
(together)
Huh?

19
00:02:12,050 --> 00:02:15,080
Japan's scariest haunted house.

20
00:02:15,080 --> 00:02:17,180
I'm really not interested
in the haunted house.

21
00:02:17,180 --> 00:02:18,210
That's 'cause you're afraid.

22
00:02:18,210 --> 00:02:20,130
-Uh-uh.
-Is too!

23
00:02:20,130 --> 00:02:22,190
(growling)

24
00:02:22,190 --> 00:02:25,060
♪

25
00:02:25,060 --> 00:02:30,040
So, how do they make sure
that it won't come and get us?

26
00:02:30,040 --> 00:02:31,030
What's that?

27
00:02:31,030 --> 00:02:33,180
A creature with
a seven-foot head.

28
00:02:33,180 --> 00:02:37,190
(screaming)

29
00:02:37,190 --> 00:02:40,020
(together)
Help, a vampire!

30
00:02:40,020 --> 00:02:42,040
(together)
Ah, a beheaded queen!

31
00:02:42,040 --> 00:02:44,060
(together)
Get off us, you goblin!

32
00:02:44,060 --> 00:02:46,050
Those three are spooked
out of their minds.

33
00:02:46,050 --> 00:02:48,110
Yeah, what a bunch
of wimps they are.

34
00:02:48,110 --> 00:02:50,070
Hm, take a look, Yoshi.

35
00:02:50,070 --> 00:02:52,240
The scary monster
reveals itself.

36
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:54,030
(laughing)

37
00:02:54,030 --> 00:02:56,290
And look at this, it's just a
rope tied to each of the wings.

38
00:02:56,290 --> 00:02:59,010
They just yank on it
a couple of times.

39
00:02:59,010 --> 00:03:01,090
Oh man, this place will
scare ya to the bone.

40
00:03:01,090 --> 00:03:03,190
Yeah, Japan's most
haunted house.

41
00:03:03,190 --> 00:03:05,110
Maybe we should go find
the girls before they run

42
00:03:05,110 --> 00:03:07,000
all the way to Tokyo.

43
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:08,220
Or dive straight into the sea.

44
00:03:08,220 --> 00:03:09,290
Are you okay?

45
00:03:09,290 --> 00:03:11,190
-Hey, we're sorry about that.
-It was an accident.

46
00:03:11,190 --> 00:03:12,270
Our friends scared
us half to death

47
00:03:12,270 --> 00:03:14,150
as some kind of stupid joke.

48
00:03:14,150 --> 00:03:16,010
Are you okay?

49
00:03:16,010 --> 00:03:17,190
(groaning)

50
00:03:17,190 --> 00:03:23,190
♪

51
00:03:23,190 --> 00:03:27,060
(indistinct conversations)

52
00:03:27,060 --> 00:03:28,090
Wow!

53
00:03:28,090 --> 00:03:30,260
Just look at all the people
waiting for this show.

54
00:03:30,260 --> 00:03:34,010
Magnificent Marimo,
the Human Cannonball.

55
00:03:34,010 --> 00:03:36,170
That's unbelievable,
let's check it out.

56
00:03:36,170 --> 00:03:39,010
Yeah, you and everybody else.

57
00:03:39,010 --> 00:03:41,030
♪

58
00:03:41,030 --> 00:03:44,000
(bull growling)

59
00:03:46,070 --> 00:03:49,140
(grunting)

60
00:03:49,140 --> 00:04:01,090
♪

61
00:04:01,090 --> 00:04:03,270
(panting)

62
00:04:03,270 --> 00:04:12,140
♪

63
00:04:12,140 --> 00:04:15,110
(crying)

64
00:04:17,070 --> 00:04:18,250
It's okay, shhh.

65
00:04:18,250 --> 00:04:21,150
That damn cannon girl is
messing with my business.

66
00:04:21,150 --> 00:04:23,220
As a matter of fact, it's
a very impressive show

67
00:04:23,220 --> 00:04:26,010
they've got there, you
should go see it, boss.

68
00:04:26,010 --> 00:04:29,020
I have, and it's
making me really mad.

69
00:04:31,210 --> 00:04:33,190
Ladies and gentlemen,
we welcome you

70
00:04:33,190 --> 00:04:35,180
to the greatest show on Earth.

71
00:04:35,180 --> 00:04:38,160
Thank you for joining
us this afternoon.

72
00:04:38,160 --> 00:04:41,240
And now without further delay,
allow me to introduce to you

73
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:45,250
the one, the only,
the Magnificent Marimo,

74
00:04:45,250 --> 00:04:48,050
the Human Cannonball!

75
00:04:48,050 --> 00:04:54,030
♪

76
00:04:54,030 --> 00:04:56,170
Wow, isn't she
absolutely beautiful?

77
00:04:56,170 --> 00:05:00,160
I hope she knows
what she's doing.

78
00:05:00,160 --> 00:05:02,060
Ta-da!

79
00:05:02,060 --> 00:05:04,290
Thank you, thank you, thank you!

80
00:05:04,290 --> 00:05:07,200
(applause)

81
00:05:07,200 --> 00:05:10,010
♪

82
00:05:10,010 --> 00:05:12,190
-I'm kind of scared for her.
-I wouldn't worry about it.

83
00:05:12,190 --> 00:05:14,130
After all, they're
professionals.

84
00:05:14,130 --> 00:05:15,260
Besides, I'm sure
they've done this act

85
00:05:15,260 --> 00:05:18,050
at least a thousand
times before.

86
00:05:18,050 --> 00:05:20,110
Begin the countdown!

87
00:05:20,110 --> 00:05:24,040
Three, two, one!

88
00:05:24,040 --> 00:05:26,270
(cannon blasting)

89
00:05:26,270 --> 00:05:30,040
(cheering)

90
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:38,020
♪

91
00:05:38,020 --> 00:05:39,040
Ta-da!

92
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:40,130
Ladies and gentlemen,
my daughter,

93
00:05:40,130 --> 00:05:42,290
the Magnificent Marimo!

94
00:05:42,290 --> 00:05:43,240
Did you hear that?

95
00:05:43,240 --> 00:05:45,080
They're a father
and daughter team.

96
00:05:45,080 --> 00:05:48,120
-Isn't that fantastic?
-Yeah, they're great performers.

97
00:05:48,120 --> 00:05:51,040
(cheering)

98
00:05:51,040 --> 00:05:52,110
Thank you!

99
00:05:52,110 --> 00:05:55,260
-Thank you!
-Ta-da!

100
00:05:55,260 --> 00:05:57,180
That's it, the show's over.

101
00:05:57,180 --> 00:06:00,010
Yeah, you heard
him, cannon girl.

102
00:06:00,010 --> 00:06:02,250
Did you hear that?

103
00:06:02,250 --> 00:06:05,000
Kenshin, why is it
you're stopping him?

104
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:08,130
Because I wanna hear exactly
what they have to say.

105
00:06:08,130 --> 00:06:09,220
Hello, Sumidaya.

106
00:06:09,220 --> 00:06:11,070
Just what are you up to?

107
00:06:11,070 --> 00:06:12,090
Hello there.

108
00:06:12,090 --> 00:06:13,250
Quite a big audience
you've packed in here

109
00:06:13,250 --> 00:06:15,220
for your show today, Jiro.

110
00:06:15,220 --> 00:06:17,050
And make no mistake about it.

111
00:06:17,050 --> 00:06:20,020
You owe me big time for all
your success and good fortune.

112
00:06:20,020 --> 00:06:23,090
We've been independent from you
Sumidaya, and you know it,

113
00:06:23,090 --> 00:06:24,250
so your threats
and intimidation

114
00:06:24,250 --> 00:06:26,200
are not about to scare me.

115
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:27,170
Think again.

116
00:06:27,170 --> 00:06:29,140
You forget you owe
me plenty of money.

117
00:06:29,140 --> 00:06:31,250
I built you up, and
I can bring you down.

118
00:06:31,250 --> 00:06:34,260
You'll either meet my
demands or you'll burn.

119
00:06:34,260 --> 00:06:36,060
Okay, I'll listen.

120
00:06:36,060 --> 00:06:39,040
I'll give you what you want,
just don't hurt my daughter.

121
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:41,150
I don't know if I can do that.

122
00:06:41,150 --> 00:06:45,140
It all depends on how
much you cooperate, Jiro.

123
00:06:45,140 --> 00:06:47,230
By the stroke of midnight
tomorrow you must pay off

124
00:06:47,230 --> 00:06:49,140
the remainder of
your debt to me,

125
00:06:49,140 --> 00:06:52,040
or surrender your
act to my operation.

126
00:06:52,040 --> 00:06:54,010
-Let's go, Hooka.
-Yes, sir.

127
00:06:54,010 --> 00:06:58,100
♪

128
00:06:58,100 --> 00:07:00,250
-Ah!
-What the hell are you doing?

129
00:07:00,250 --> 00:07:04,040
No one messes with me.

130
00:07:04,040 --> 00:07:06,060
Quickly, we've gotta put it out!

131
00:07:06,060 --> 00:07:08,080
Did you see that
look on his face?

132
00:07:08,080 --> 00:07:11,050
Yeah, as frightened
as a circus mouse!

133
00:07:11,050 --> 00:07:13,180
-I just don't like those guys.
-Huh?

134
00:07:13,180 --> 00:07:16,000
They shouldn't intimidate
people like that.

135
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:18,210
Come on, let's get 'em!

136
00:07:18,210 --> 00:07:21,190
-Hey, where's Yoshi?
-He's right down there.

137
00:07:21,190 --> 00:07:25,040
(grunting)

138
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:26,010
-Ah!
-Oh, hi.

139
00:07:26,010 --> 00:07:27,050
I didn't mean to bump you.

140
00:07:27,050 --> 00:07:29,220
Yoshi is my name, and I just
want you to know that was

141
00:07:29,220 --> 00:07:33,060
absolutely incredible when you
got shot out of that cannon.

142
00:07:33,060 --> 00:07:35,230
Thanks, I'm Marimo,
and thanks too

143
00:07:35,230 --> 00:07:38,210
for helping me put
out the fire, Yogi.

144
00:07:38,210 --> 00:07:40,120
It's Yoshi!

145
00:07:40,120 --> 00:07:41,250
(laughing)

146
00:07:45,080 --> 00:07:48,130
So, you've fallen for the
cannon girl, huh Yoshi?

147
00:07:48,130 --> 00:07:51,040
It's always obvious when
your cheeks turn red.

148
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:53,010
Her real name is Marimo,

149
00:07:53,010 --> 00:07:54,200
and she's just
a new friend of mine.

150
00:07:54,200 --> 00:07:57,290
Why you old
cannon-kissing Romeo.

151
00:07:57,290 --> 00:08:02,090
-I smell love in the air!
-Mhm, mmm.

152
00:08:02,090 --> 00:08:04,290
-Hey, wait, where are you going?
-Out for a walk.

153
00:08:04,290 --> 00:08:06,190
Yeah, and that
full moon outside

154
00:08:06,190 --> 00:08:09,110
might make you feel
even more romantic.

155
00:08:10,280 --> 00:08:11,290
Poor Yoshi.

156
00:08:11,290 --> 00:08:14,100
He's gotta learn to take
a joke a little better.

157
00:08:14,100 --> 00:08:16,060
Do you think he's all right?

158
00:08:16,060 --> 00:08:18,090
He must be worried about Marimo.

159
00:08:18,090 --> 00:08:21,000
He really hates it when
people get pushed around.

160
00:08:23,050 --> 00:08:26,100
Don't worry, Marimo,
everything will be all right.

161
00:08:28,120 --> 00:08:30,010
-Oh, hey!
-Hey!

162
00:08:30,010 --> 00:08:31,160
Watch where you're going!

163
00:08:31,160 --> 00:08:34,120
Huh, my wallet!

164
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:37,130
(panting)

165
00:08:37,130 --> 00:08:39,270
Hey, come back here you thief!

166
00:08:39,270 --> 00:08:42,240
(crashing)

167
00:08:44,280 --> 00:08:48,210
Father, are you all right?

168
00:08:48,210 --> 00:08:50,070
It's going to be okay.

169
00:08:50,070 --> 00:08:52,622
Help, he--

170
00:08:52,622 --> 00:08:53,642
Who are you?

171
00:08:53,642 --> 00:08:55,080
What do you want?

172
00:08:55,080 --> 00:08:57,210
Guess.

173
00:08:57,210 --> 00:08:59,270
(screaming)

174
00:08:59,270 --> 00:09:00,290
Huh?

175
00:09:00,290 --> 00:09:05,000
♪

176
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:06,190
Hey, let go of me!

177
00:09:06,190 --> 00:09:10,150
It looks like you won't be
able to make tomorrow's show.

178
00:09:10,150 --> 00:09:12,280
Tough luck, my
little flying friend.

179
00:09:12,280 --> 00:09:14,080
Hey, back off!

180
00:09:14,080 --> 00:09:15,220
(together)
Huh?

181
00:09:15,220 --> 00:09:18,180
-Oh, help me, Yogi!
-You mean Yoshi!

182
00:09:18,180 --> 00:09:22,130
♪

183
00:09:22,130 --> 00:09:23,280
That's it, punk.

184
00:09:23,280 --> 00:09:26,060
This punk will kill
you if necessary.

185
00:09:26,060 --> 00:09:28,160
♪

186
00:09:28,160 --> 00:09:29,270
Come here!

187
00:09:29,270 --> 00:09:38,160
♪

188
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:40,220
-You'll pay for this.
-I'm out of here.

189
00:09:40,220 --> 00:09:43,060
Come back here, I'll--huh?

190
00:09:43,060 --> 00:09:45,180
Please help me,
my father is hurt.

191
00:09:45,180 --> 00:09:47,200
Then we must hurry.

192
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:49,090
All right, there.

193
00:09:51,160 --> 00:09:54,030
That will protect your
wounds, and help you heal.

194
00:09:54,030 --> 00:09:55,090
Good.

195
00:09:55,090 --> 00:09:57,210
With this sling, at least I'll
be able to perform tonight.

196
00:09:57,210 --> 00:09:59,080
Father, you have to rest.

197
00:09:59,080 --> 00:10:01,090
You were hurt very badly.

198
00:10:01,090 --> 00:10:04,090
I know that Sumidaya
is to blame for this.

199
00:10:04,090 --> 00:10:05,180
I'm going to the police.

200
00:10:05,180 --> 00:10:07,270
I am not going to the
police without any proof,

201
00:10:07,270 --> 00:10:10,150
and we need the money from
tomorrow night's show.

202
00:10:10,150 --> 00:10:12,060
But what should we do?

203
00:10:12,060 --> 00:10:14,190
I'm not about to stand by
here and watch these goons

204
00:10:14,190 --> 00:10:17,080
try to pressure you into
losing your business.

205
00:10:17,080 --> 00:10:19,020
Yoshi, you don't understand.

206
00:10:19,020 --> 00:10:22,270
I am legally obligated to pay
the debt I owe to Sumidaya.

207
00:10:22,270 --> 00:10:25,200
You see, with the money we
could make from tomorrow's show,

208
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:28,180
we might just be able to pay
off the balance of our loan.

209
00:10:28,180 --> 00:10:31,080
When I get a hold of these
guys, I'm gonna make them pay!

210
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:33,110
I've got to get up
and make sure that--

211
00:10:33,110 --> 00:10:36,000
Sir, you must stay still.

212
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:37,050
Listen, Father.

213
00:10:37,050 --> 00:10:40,210
I've decided I'm going to put
the show on all by myself.

214
00:10:40,210 --> 00:10:42,140
No, you're not.

215
00:10:42,140 --> 00:10:45,140
-Wha--wha--how come?
-Because I said so!

216
00:10:45,140 --> 00:10:47,200
If you make the smallest
mistake, it's possible

217
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:49,190
you may never be
able to walk again.

218
00:10:49,190 --> 00:10:51,210
-But--
-I know my way's the best,

219
00:10:51,210 --> 00:10:55,050
and you must believe
and trust what I say.

220
00:10:55,050 --> 00:10:57,170
Sir, I can help out,
I'm smart and brave.

221
00:10:57,170 --> 00:11:01,110
I'm sorry but using gunpowder
is much too dangerous.

222
00:11:01,110 --> 00:11:04,150
Hey, you know what,
I'm a pretty good cook.

223
00:11:04,150 --> 00:11:05,130
(together)
Huh?

224
00:11:05,130 --> 00:11:06,270
Just show me the exact recipe,

225
00:11:06,270 --> 00:11:08,230
and I'm sure I
can bake it right.

226
00:11:10,210 --> 00:11:20,090
♪

227
00:11:20,090 --> 00:11:23,060
-I smell blood.
-Doesn't it smell sweet?

228
00:11:23,060 --> 00:11:26,020
Even sweeter than cotton candy.

229
00:11:26,020 --> 00:11:28,110
Yeah, and it's even
better if it's the blood

230
00:11:28,110 --> 00:11:30,140
of someone I just murdered.

231
00:11:30,140 --> 00:11:33,080
-Are you sleeping?
-Not anymore.

232
00:11:33,080 --> 00:11:35,290
I was having a
dream about death,

233
00:11:35,290 --> 00:11:38,290
about breaking someone's neck,
about twisting it slowly

234
00:11:38,290 --> 00:11:42,010
until I feel it
snap in my hands.

235
00:11:42,010 --> 00:11:43,140
And then hanging
them from a tree

236
00:11:43,140 --> 00:11:46,210
for me to slice
their guts out.

237
00:11:46,210 --> 00:11:49,180
-No business again!
-Don't worry, boss.

238
00:11:49,180 --> 00:11:52,030
Jirokichi is in real bad
shape, he'll never be able

239
00:11:52,030 --> 00:11:54,040
to do the show
in his condition.

240
00:11:54,040 --> 00:11:55,170
Watch, you'll see.

241
00:11:55,170 --> 00:11:57,060
He'll come crawling
back begging,

242
00:11:57,060 --> 00:11:59,170
"Please take us
back, I'm sorry."

243
00:11:59,170 --> 00:12:02,010
Just like that, and we'll
be back in business.

244
00:12:02,010 --> 00:12:04,280
I hope you're right,
but I can't be sure.

245
00:12:04,280 --> 00:12:08,030
It's impossible for the girl to
do the show without her father.

246
00:12:08,030 --> 00:12:10,260
She's a stubborn girl who might
attempt it all by herself.

247
00:12:10,260 --> 00:12:12,180
You must make sure
she doesn't pull it off.

248
00:12:12,180 --> 00:12:13,240
Yes, sir.

249
00:12:13,240 --> 00:12:15,100
Why don't you
put me in charge,

250
00:12:15,100 --> 00:12:17,270
and give us a chance
to handle the situation?

251
00:12:17,270 --> 00:12:20,050
Because you'd kill them
at the first opportunity,

252
00:12:20,050 --> 00:12:22,080
and I need them to
make me my money.

253
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:25,050
(laughing)

254
00:12:26,100 --> 00:12:29,050
Ladies and gentlemen,
step right up!

255
00:12:29,050 --> 00:12:33,060
Step right up, the show will
begin in just five minutes!

256
00:12:33,060 --> 00:12:37,010
The Magnificent
Marimo flies again!

257
00:12:37,010 --> 00:12:38,260
Damn, I knew it.

258
00:12:38,260 --> 00:12:41,230
We'll just see
how far she'll fly.

259
00:12:43,100 --> 00:12:45,020
What are you doing
up there, my friend?

260
00:12:45,020 --> 00:12:46,130
Hey, guys, bad news.

261
00:12:46,130 --> 00:12:48,090
Marimo's father got
mugged last night.

262
00:12:48,090 --> 00:12:49,140
Oh, really?

263
00:12:49,140 --> 00:12:51,010
So does anybody
know who did it?

264
00:12:51,010 --> 00:12:52,260
I'm really sure
it was Sumidaya.

265
00:12:52,260 --> 00:12:55,020
And let me guess, you're
here to save the day,

266
00:12:55,020 --> 00:12:57,160
and win the heart
of your fair maiden.

267
00:12:57,160 --> 00:12:59,140
I'm sorry, but that was funny.

268
00:12:59,140 --> 00:13:02,020
Can you two stop teasing
Yoshi for a minute?

269
00:13:02,020 --> 00:13:03,150
But we're just having fun.

270
00:13:03,150 --> 00:13:05,260
It's a good thing her
father's okay, or I might--

271
00:13:05,260 --> 00:13:08,090
Decapitate me with
a spinning back fist?

272
00:13:08,090 --> 00:13:09,130
-You better run!
-You better run!

273
00:13:09,130 --> 00:13:11,070
(laughing)

274
00:13:11,070 --> 00:13:14,200
-Yoshi, we've got a problem.
-What's wrong, Marimo?

275
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:17,050
Help me, it's disappeared.

276
00:13:17,050 --> 00:13:19,150
-They stole the gunpowder!
-What?

277
00:13:19,150 --> 00:13:20,210
What do we do?

278
00:13:20,210 --> 00:13:22,100
Well, we'll just have
to find some more,

279
00:13:22,100 --> 00:13:24,030
because the show must go on.

280
00:13:24,030 --> 00:13:25,280
-I have an idea.
-Huh?

281
00:13:25,280 --> 00:13:28,250
We can get the gunpowder you
need from a fireworks shop.

282
00:13:28,250 --> 00:13:30,180
This area of town has
a whole bunch of them

283
00:13:30,180 --> 00:13:32,020
that might help you out.

284
00:13:32,020 --> 00:13:33,240
Come on!

285
00:13:35,250 --> 00:13:36,230
We have to hurry!

286
00:13:36,230 --> 00:13:39,250
I'm right behind you!

287
00:13:39,250 --> 00:13:41,280
I hope they make it back
or all these people

288
00:13:41,280 --> 00:13:43,250
are gonna get very impatient.

289
00:13:43,250 --> 00:13:45,280
Then we'll have to stall
them until they get back.

290
00:13:45,280 --> 00:13:47,020
-Uh-oh.
-Huh?

291
00:13:47,020 --> 00:13:49,130
We'll just put on our own show!

292
00:13:49,130 --> 00:13:51,220
I, uh, think I've
got stage fright.

293
00:13:51,220 --> 00:13:53,110
Are we getting
paid for this?

294
00:13:53,110 --> 00:13:56,000
(indistinct remarks)

295
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:58,120
Hey, come on,
let's start the show!

296
00:13:58,120 --> 00:14:02,170
Hey, why don't you just
give us back our money!

297
00:14:02,170 --> 00:14:06,100
-Are you guys ready to go on?
-Well, if you say so.

298
00:14:06,100 --> 00:14:08,060
Just don't make me dance.

299
00:14:08,060 --> 00:14:10,230
Ladies and gentlemen, thank
you very much for coming,

300
00:14:10,230 --> 00:14:13,100
and welcome to the
greatest show on earth!

301
00:14:13,100 --> 00:14:16,030
Magnificent Marimo
the Human Cannonball

302
00:14:16,030 --> 00:14:19,090
will perform in
just a few minutes!

303
00:14:19,090 --> 00:14:22,010
-I really hope this works.
-It will.

304
00:14:22,010 --> 00:14:24,220
-Or we'll blow sky high.
-Don't worry, Yumi.

305
00:14:24,220 --> 00:14:27,130
♪

306
00:14:27,130 --> 00:14:29,080
Before we get to
the main attraction,

307
00:14:29,080 --> 00:14:30,270
we have a surprise for you.

308
00:14:30,270 --> 00:14:34,290
Please give a warm welcome
to Kenshin and his ball!

309
00:14:34,290 --> 00:14:37,090
Oh, yeah, this should
be a piece of cake.

310
00:14:37,090 --> 00:14:40,230
Here, maybe this
will help for balance.

311
00:14:40,230 --> 00:14:42,290
What am I supposed
to do with this thing?

312
00:14:42,290 --> 00:14:44,250
Here goes nothing.

313
00:14:44,250 --> 00:14:50,190
♪

314
00:14:50,190 --> 00:14:52,090
Hey, use the umbrella, Kenshin!

315
00:14:52,090 --> 00:14:54,050
Yeah, just open it up!

316
00:14:54,050 --> 00:14:56,100
Help me, somebody help me!

317
00:14:56,100 --> 00:14:59,260
Here, try this
ball, it might help.

318
00:14:59,260 --> 00:15:02,170
(shouting)

319
00:15:02,170 --> 00:15:08,040
♪

320
00:15:08,040 --> 00:15:11,060
-Oh, that must have hurt.
-Ouch.

321
00:15:11,060 --> 00:15:13,210
That was absolutely
amazing, Kenshin.

322
00:15:13,210 --> 00:15:16,200
Good, can you help me
stand up Manipuki?

323
00:15:16,200 --> 00:15:19,170
(applause and cheering)

324
00:15:24,180 --> 00:15:26,130
-Thank you!
-Yeah, thanks!

325
00:15:26,130 --> 00:15:30,020
-We can make it.
-Let's go!

326
00:15:30,020 --> 00:15:32,290
(birds chirping)

327
00:15:36,220 --> 00:15:38,230
Marimo.

328
00:15:38,230 --> 00:15:41,250
♪

329
00:15:41,250 --> 00:15:44,240
Okay, just aim at the target,
and make 'em all count.

330
00:15:44,240 --> 00:15:47,190
Hold it, what's gonna
happen if she hits me?

331
00:15:47,190 --> 00:15:49,000
That's not a problem, Sano.

332
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:50,290
Then I'll just have
to mop up the blood.

333
00:15:50,290 --> 00:15:52,210
This is show business?

334
00:15:52,210 --> 00:15:54,110
Go ahead, Kaoru,
he's just scared.

335
00:15:54,110 --> 00:15:56,040
I am not scared!

336
00:15:56,040 --> 00:15:58,260
Now, Kaoru, you have
done this before, right?

337
00:15:58,260 --> 00:16:00,160
♪

338
00:16:00,160 --> 00:16:01,090
No.

339
00:16:01,090 --> 00:16:04,030
(gasping)

340
00:16:04,030 --> 00:16:05,210
I'm gonna kill you!

341
00:16:05,210 --> 00:16:08,280
(yelling)

342
00:16:08,280 --> 00:16:11,200
(whimpering)

343
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:14,030
Oh man, Sano, you're bleeding!

344
00:16:14,030 --> 00:16:16,080
(grunting)

345
00:16:16,080 --> 00:16:18,200
Kenshin, go get him!

346
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:21,110
-Sano, get back here!
-The show must go on!

347
00:16:21,110 --> 00:16:24,080
(crowd laughing)

348
00:16:25,190 --> 00:16:27,100
Let's see the cannon girl!

349
00:16:27,100 --> 00:16:31,100
Yeah, we wanna see
the cannon girl!

350
00:16:31,100 --> 00:16:34,110
I just hope Yoshi will hurry.

351
00:16:34,110 --> 00:16:37,160
We're almost there.

352
00:16:37,160 --> 00:16:40,050
Yoshi!

353
00:16:40,050 --> 00:16:43,150
I'm extremely sorry about
tripping you, my little friend.

354
00:16:43,150 --> 00:16:45,200
Yeah, I bet.

355
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:47,270
I want that bag of
stuff right now.

356
00:16:47,270 --> 00:16:49,110
Then come and get it.

357
00:16:49,110 --> 00:16:50,230
I'll just take that.

358
00:16:50,230 --> 00:16:52,090
Hey, give me--

359
00:16:52,090 --> 00:16:55,090
(grunting)

360
00:16:55,090 --> 00:16:57,260
-Come on!
-Ha, see ya!

361
00:16:57,260 --> 00:16:59,210
You idiot, go get those kids!

362
00:17:00,240 --> 00:17:03,260
♪ I dream of Genie

363
00:17:03,260 --> 00:17:08,000
with the light
brown hair ♪♪

364
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:11,080
(singing gibberish)

365
00:17:11,080 --> 00:17:19,020
♪

366
00:17:19,020 --> 00:17:21,150
Hey, get off the stage, loser!

367
00:17:21,150 --> 00:17:25,100
Hey, you, give us back our money
or we'll set this tent on fire!

368
00:17:25,100 --> 00:17:29,030
(crowd yelling and boo-ing)

369
00:17:29,030 --> 00:17:30,190
We're in trouble now.

370
00:17:30,190 --> 00:17:33,200
I don't get it, I thought this
audience would love some music.

371
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:36,230
-Kenshin!
-They're back!

372
00:17:36,230 --> 00:17:37,260
Oh my gosh!

373
00:17:37,260 --> 00:17:40,150
Kenshin, take 'em!

374
00:17:40,150 --> 00:17:41,140
It's Sumidaya.

375
00:17:41,140 --> 00:17:44,040
Yeah, and he's brought
four stooges along.

376
00:17:44,040 --> 00:17:45,210
That's it, I've had it.

377
00:17:45,210 --> 00:17:47,270
I'm sick and tired
of you gang of morons

378
00:17:47,270 --> 00:17:49,280
messing around in
my personal business,

379
00:17:49,280 --> 00:17:52,260
and putting your fat heads
in where they don't belong!

380
00:17:52,260 --> 00:17:54,220
And I've decided
I'm going to make sure

381
00:17:54,220 --> 00:17:56,190
that none of you
ever walk again!

382
00:17:56,190 --> 00:17:58,200
Kill 'em!

383
00:18:03,110 --> 00:18:04,210
Can't you do better than that?

384
00:18:04,210 --> 00:18:06,050
I got it.

385
00:18:06,050 --> 00:18:09,130
Don't worry.

386
00:18:09,130 --> 00:18:12,200
-Nice save, Sanosuke.
-No problem.

387
00:18:12,200 --> 00:18:14,100
I'm going to slice
you to pieces.

388
00:18:14,100 --> 00:18:16,130
After I've poked
him full of holes.

389
00:18:16,130 --> 00:18:18,180
And I've pulled
off his damn head.

390
00:18:18,180 --> 00:18:20,290
If you guys fight as
well as you threaten to,

391
00:18:20,290 --> 00:18:22,190
then you're the ones
who should worry.

392
00:18:22,190 --> 00:18:25,210
I don't think you're getting
the message, here it is.

393
00:18:25,210 --> 00:18:29,100
I wouldn't underestimate these
three assassins if I were you.

394
00:18:29,100 --> 00:18:31,230
-That's because I--
-Shut your mouth!

395
00:18:31,230 --> 00:18:34,020
Well, we'll see who
has the last word.

396
00:18:34,020 --> 00:18:35,050
Hold it.

397
00:18:35,050 --> 00:18:37,100
Just remember what
you did before,

398
00:18:37,100 --> 00:18:39,130
and take this umbrella.

399
00:18:39,130 --> 00:18:40,230
Okay.

400
00:18:40,230 --> 00:18:42,130
Ladies and gentlemen,

401
00:18:42,130 --> 00:18:46,190
Shabubula and his secret
hit-and-miss dance style!

402
00:18:46,190 --> 00:18:49,120
(cheering)

403
00:18:49,120 --> 00:18:50,280
You heard her.

404
00:18:50,280 --> 00:18:53,050
Observe, you just
might learn something.

405
00:18:53,050 --> 00:18:56,010
-Oh, man.
-Just what's he gonna do?

406
00:18:56,010 --> 00:18:58,070
(yelling)

407
00:18:58,070 --> 00:19:00,060
The umbrella spin!

408
00:19:02,120 --> 00:19:05,040
That was close!

409
00:19:05,040 --> 00:19:07,020
A hit-and-ball toss!

410
00:19:07,020 --> 00:19:10,100
(yelling)

411
00:19:10,100 --> 00:19:13,080
(cheering)

412
00:19:13,080 --> 00:19:15,080
(grunting)

413
00:19:15,080 --> 00:19:22,030
♪

414
00:19:22,030 --> 00:19:26,140
-Oh, my cannon!
-Get this thing off me!

415
00:19:26,140 --> 00:19:29,260
-Nice try, baldy!
-Almost, bird brain.

416
00:19:29,260 --> 00:19:33,210
I said kill 'em!

417
00:19:33,210 --> 00:19:37,100
Watch the pretty umbrella,
ya stupid buffoon.

418
00:19:37,100 --> 00:19:38,240
Hey, Sano, catch!

419
00:19:38,240 --> 00:19:40,280
Hi there!

420
00:19:40,280 --> 00:19:42,250
-Yoshi, some rope!
-Got it!

421
00:19:42,250 --> 00:19:43,290
Don't just stand there.

422
00:19:43,290 --> 00:19:46,150
Draw your sword,
and prepare to die.

423
00:19:46,150 --> 00:19:48,150
This umbrella is enough.

424
00:19:48,150 --> 00:19:50,270
That arrogance will
make you a dead man

425
00:19:50,270 --> 00:19:52,280
with your bleeding
heart in my hand.

426
00:19:52,280 --> 00:19:54,020
We'll see.

427
00:19:54,020 --> 00:19:57,210
♪

428
00:19:57,210 --> 00:20:00,180
-I'm--
-Hey, I'm right up here!

429
00:20:00,180 --> 00:20:01,250
(groaning)

430
00:20:04,160 --> 00:20:06,120
(cheering)

431
00:20:06,120 --> 00:20:08,140
All that with an umbrella?

432
00:20:08,140 --> 00:20:10,140
(yelling)

433
00:20:10,140 --> 00:20:12,190
I got him, he's all mine!

434
00:20:12,190 --> 00:20:14,200
♪

435
00:20:14,200 --> 00:20:17,170
(speaking gibberish)

436
00:20:21,110 --> 00:20:24,050
Sumidaya!

437
00:20:24,050 --> 00:20:25,170
You go get him, Marimo!

438
00:20:25,170 --> 00:20:27,240
All set?

439
00:20:27,240 --> 00:20:30,010
Yes.

440
00:20:30,010 --> 00:20:33,080
(cannon blasting)

441
00:20:33,080 --> 00:20:38,040
♪

442
00:20:38,040 --> 00:20:39,240
Bullseye!

443
00:20:39,240 --> 00:20:42,180
(cheering)

444
00:20:42,180 --> 00:20:49,100
♪

445
00:20:49,100 --> 00:20:51,070
Just listen to that crowd, huh?

446
00:20:51,070 --> 00:20:52,140
Well, they loved me.

447
00:20:52,140 --> 00:20:54,130
Yeah, but not as
much as they loved me.

448
00:20:54,130 --> 00:20:56,150
They loved the
whole performance.

449
00:20:56,150 --> 00:20:59,060
♪

450
00:20:59,060 --> 00:21:01,180
This time, Sumidaya, you're
going to have to pay for all

451
00:21:01,180 --> 00:21:04,090
your crimes, and go to jail,
ya miserable scoundrel.

452
00:21:04,090 --> 00:21:08,260
♪

453
00:21:08,260 --> 00:21:11,180
They'll be locked up
for a really long time.

454
00:21:11,180 --> 00:21:13,220
Hey, how about if all you guys

455
00:21:13,220 --> 00:21:16,020
become a permanent
part of my show?

456
00:21:16,020 --> 00:21:18,270
Well, I could become a
professional knife thrower

457
00:21:18,270 --> 00:21:21,100
if Kenshin and Sano
would volunteer.

458
00:21:21,100 --> 00:21:23,140
(laughing)

459
00:21:23,140 --> 00:21:25,160
Hey, you two, where
are you going?

460
00:21:25,160 --> 00:21:27,180
I'm retiring from show business!

461
00:21:27,180 --> 00:21:29,080
I've got a train to catch!

462
00:21:29,080 --> 00:21:31,250
♪

463
00:21:31,250 --> 00:21:34,110
Aw, come on guys!

464
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:38,200
♪

465
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:42,080
(singing in foreign language)

466
00:21:42,080 --> 00:23:10,280
♪

